technical_description:
All data pertains to the timeframe of 5 May 2020 - 5 June 2020.

Let $X_{cu} $ be the sparse matrix such that $x_{cu}$ is (roughly, up to API limitations) the total number of minutes user $u$ has spent in channel $c$. 

Let $X'_{cu}$ be the user-wise (column-wise) normalized version of $\ X_{cu} $. Then the similarity between channel $c_1$ and $c_2$ is given by the cosine similarity between the corresponding rows:

$$sim(c_1, c_2) =  rac{X'_{c_1}X'_{c_2}}{\Vert X'_{c_1} \Vert \Vert X'_{c_2} \Vert} $$

Embeddings are created using the UMAP dimension reduction technique to 2D/3D, and clusters are found with HDBSCAN in a 6D embedding space.
